Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.63,0:00:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, Corinna, why are your letters\Never so short?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.63,0:00:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"As with Eupolis the astro...astro,\Nastrologist, you drive my heart mad."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.14,0:00:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"Even the gold of ideas fades,\Nand the work of Galonius..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.68,0:00:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.62,0:00:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that there's no need\Nto read any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.19,0:00:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Is there something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough from you. Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.66,0:00:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm very sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.80,0:00:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I do something to upset you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.73,0:00:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who cannot\Npronounce Latin correctly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.07,0:00:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,do not have the right to\Nread books to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.07,0:00:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be careful next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.88,0:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:02:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You got quite the scolding\Nat the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, Mr. Business Admin\NStudent, Karl Neumann!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know who I am?\NWho are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Lotte Frank.\NI'm in cultural anthropology.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.34,0:03:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you read books for him\Npart-time as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.78,0:03:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I look after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He only has male students\Nread to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.15,0:03:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in charge of Tuesdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Other students read to him\Non other days. He can barely see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the mysterious tycoon,\NHans Georg Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.17,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know. I jumped at the job\Nbecause the pay was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.61,0:03:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard all the rumors\Nabout him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.85,0:03:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's said that he can control the stocks\Nof businesses throughout Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.12,0:03:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with a single phone call\Nfrom his mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:03:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He's called\Nthe Howard Hughes of Bavaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He has no family!\NThere's no one close to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.43,0:04:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But his fortune continues to grow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.13,0:04:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think he's going to do\Nwith that money?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.70,0:04:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.73,0:04:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's an even greater mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.33,0:04:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,His other nickname is\N"The Vampire of Bavaria."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.70,0:04:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Vampire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When the bell tolls at 2:00 AM,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,he drives into town with his butler\Nin a hearse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.21,0:04:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like something\Nfrom a gothic horror story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.52,0:04:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably just taking a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.32,0:04:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to find out soon\Nif he really is just taking a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.66,0:04:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "find out"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.99,0:04:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for my research paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.10,0:04:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Intellectual Activities\Nof Medieval and Present-day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Business Men of Bavaria."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be a great sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.77,0:04:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why you looked me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.31,0:04:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I just looked up\Nyour name and department.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't worry that\NSchuwald yelled at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.61,0:04:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He says mean things\Nto all the other students.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I'm used to being\Nyelled at and being hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah. I was shunted around to\Ndifferent foster homes as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.79,0:05:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, you're not from\Nany of the local prep schools, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.63,0:05:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You really did look me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.40,0:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So you don't have parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.51,0:05:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to this university in Munich
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.14,0:05:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought I could\Nmeet my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom's in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, did you meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.99,0:05:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.42,0:05:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know your mom's name,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.79,0:05:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.96,0:05:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.57,0:05:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm already interested.\NI'm going to find out anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.77,0:05:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.21,0:05:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.11,0:06:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be easy to find her\Nif you know that much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Go meet her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.31,0:06:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom will be delighted!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I said...it doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.75,0:06:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.99,0:06:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"His dash, like a chestnut mare"'
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"gathered thunder in his blood\Nand caused great waves..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.37,0:06:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand listening to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.47,0:06:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I only love beautiful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.51,0:06:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand listening to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me something\Nso important?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked up your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.26,0:06:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it doesn't matter anymore,\Ndidn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl... Is there some way\NI can help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.53,0:06:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.47,0:07:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...you said that you were\Ngoing to find out where
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans Schuwald goes at night,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.01,0:07:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I go with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.89,0:07:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, of course!\NIt'd be great if you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.99,0:07:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, it's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.49,0:07:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the greatest scoop since
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the Supernatural Phenomenon\NResearch Group was started.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.50,0:07:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.23,0:07:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there's no mistake that\Nthis poem was written in 1502
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.40,0:07:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by Bishop Gropius, one of\Nthe founders of this university!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.41,0:07:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This verse is the important part!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.88,0:07:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"On the second to the last great year"'
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.41,0:07:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Thursday's boy will\Ncome to this land"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.48,0:07:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"and the books shall be\Nengulfed in flames."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.49,0:07:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"The entire world will be\Nengulfed in sorrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.09,0:07:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:07:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. "The second\Nto the last great year."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.37,0:08:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 1996.\NIn other words, this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.80,0:08:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The "great year" is a leap year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The only leap year after this one\Nin this century is the year 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.21,0:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He will "come to this land"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.48,0:08:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"and the books shall be\Nengulfed in flames."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"The books of this land" means that\Nthis university is going to burn down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.99,0:08:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what's "Thursday's boy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thursday, or Donnerstag,\Ncomes from the word, "Donner."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.66,0:08:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, "thunder."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.13,0:08:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that\Nit's the god of thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty far-fetched!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.73,0:08:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.40,0:08:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the feature of our next bulletin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.50,0:08:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind printing this,\Nbut who's going to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that a god of destruction\Nis coming to this university?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Vampire of Bavaria, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.09,0:09:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the truth behind\Nhis mysterious prowling?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How disillusioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.41,0:09:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How stupid. I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.94,0:09:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.48,0:09:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.24,0:09:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.05,0:09:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.52,0:09:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's not do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.73,0:09:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This isn't a place for a girl.\NGo home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.53,0:09:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"I only love beautiful things."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.67,0:09:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know\Nhow pathetic a man he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.28,0:09:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for a girl,\Nyou've come to the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I retired a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.17,0:10:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You should introduce yourself first\Nwhen you go to someone else's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.41,0:10:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like students.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.18,0:10:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working part-time\Nfor Hans Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he... Why does\NHans Schuwald come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.73,0:10:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Or so I'd like to say, but it seems like\Nhe can't function down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:10:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes to give me money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.91,0:11:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.38,0:11:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He wept and apologized to me\Nwhen I told him my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.62,0:11:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He made me bear a child\Nand threw me out like trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.22,0:11:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl...could it be that\Nyou're Hans Schuwald's child?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie. You're...you're...\Nnot Margot Langer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!\NIt was in the newspaper a year ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"Former Prostitute"... Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Former Prostitute, Margot Langer,\NMurdered. Culprit Still Unknown."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.98,0:11:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother is already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You used that to pretend to be\Nmy mother...Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.59,0:11:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could swindle money\Nfrom Hans Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.16,0:11:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.90,0:11:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He pays me knowing that\NI'm not the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.50,0:12:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that the real Margot,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.27,0:12:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the one he should be\Npaying money to,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.37,0:12:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is no longer in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is his way of atoning\Nfor what he did to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.94,0:12:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, money, money!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.21,0:12:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He lived only for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.81,0:12:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.65,0:12:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk big, but people\Naren't that different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an old man without much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.19,0:12:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You should tell him that you're\Nhis son and get that huge fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.77,0:12:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.17,0:12:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You call me a liar, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not so sure about you, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.21,0:12:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another boy\Nwho says that he's his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.48,0:12:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He came here like you did\Nand had the same story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.92,0:12:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No way. It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie. He's lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who's lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.90,0:13:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Both look like fakes to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.67,0:13:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You take turns during the week\Nto read books to Schuwald, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.11,0:13:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He's one of the readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.62,0:13:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I believe he was Thursday's boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you tell her\Nthat you're the real one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I...I was shunted around to\Ndifferent foster homes as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.44,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.74,0:13:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But my current foster parents\Nare really good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.38,0:13:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how grateful I am to them,\Nit's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I want to meet\Nmy real parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.72,0:13:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought by learning how pathetic\Nmy real father was
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.82,0:14:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I could love my current foster parents\Nfrom the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.76,0:14:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.77,0:14:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen\NThursday's boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.70,0:14:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off on Thursdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.37,0:14:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But once, I went to\Nget something I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.38,0:14:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.18,0:14:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.98,0:14:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was blond and had\Na very handsome face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is Thursday's boy?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.33,0:14:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There is someone in this university\Nwho is pretending to be me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.97,0:14:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Listen, Karl.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.21,0:14:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Listen well to what\Nyour mother has to say!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.41,0:14:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take this money and ride the train\Nat Platform 5.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.45,0:14:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Get off at the eighth station.\NThere will be a lady called Marta.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What about you, Mom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.68,0:15:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I told you that I can't go with you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.36,0:15:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are the police after you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll stay with you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.63,0:15:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.46,0:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You'll be put in the orphanage here,\Nif you stay with me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.40,0:15:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You'll continue to be called\Na prostitute's child if you stay here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.34,0:15:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, quickly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What about Dad?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.01,0:15:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My dad is Hans Georg Schuwald,\Nisn't he?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.01,0:15:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who told you that?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mrs. Bella from across the street\Ntold me so.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.38,0:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's really rich, isn't he?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She said that he abandoned me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You weren't abandoned!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.83,0:15:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then I'm going to where Dad is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not right now!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.90,0:15:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When would be okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.57,0:15:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When you're bigger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.90,0:15:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you're an adult\Nand still want to meet him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But you mustn't expect anything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.71,0:16:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You mustn't hate him\Neven if he's cold to you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.31,0:16:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.79,0:16:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because I don't hate him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take this with you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.10,0:16:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is something your father\Ngave you when you were born.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.47,0:16:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, I found out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.91,0:16:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out who Thursday's boy is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.28,0:16:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Edmund Fahren!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a student from\Nthe literature department.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.59,0:16:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He's working part-time\Nreading books at Schuwald's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.12,0:16:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in charge of Thursdays!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.46,0:16:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund Fahren...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.16,0:16:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is!\NThis class has just finished a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Say!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.04,0:17:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.07,0:17:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.81,0:17:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund! Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.91,0:17:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.25,0:17:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't come to class today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.72,0:17:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.12,0:17:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only a matter of time\Nbefore we catch that fraud.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who's going to inherit\NSchuwald's great fortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.20,0:17:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.73,0:17:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.00,0:17:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,His fortune doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.54,0:17:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.51,0:17:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald can have all the money\Nsucked out of him...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.61,0:17:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But...I can't forgive\Nthis Edmund Fahren
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.12,0:17:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for saying that he's my mom's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.83,0:18:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"As the petals of your silk flowers\Nwhich swayed in the breeze"'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.80,0:18:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"the mockingbird cried in my heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not saying anything today,\NMr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.31,0:18:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I yell at you so much.\NWhy don't you quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.39,0:18:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because the money is good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.56,0:18:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.13,0:18:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is money the only thing\Nyou can talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.04,0:18:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are your parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.31,0:18:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was taken in by foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.55,0:18:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I asked you\Nsomething unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to meet\Nyour real parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.39,0:19:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that boy who came to me\Nis the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.43,0:19:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not after money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.77,0:19:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.84,0:19:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm just talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.14,0:19:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, also...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.88,0:19:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Latin has gotten better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.72,0:19:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.84,0:19:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that Edmund Fahren\Nis absent again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.61,0:19:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably in bed with the cold.\NHonestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.41,0:19:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be hasty.\NTomorrow is Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.18,0:19:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll go to Schuwald's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.52,0:20:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to expose him\Nright in front of Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.92,0:20:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it! Let's get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.23,0:20:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,An hour has already passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.30,0:20:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If he has a cold,\Nwe can attack him in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.80,0:20:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.37,0:20:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to barge into his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.97,0:20:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You even looked up\NFahren's address?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.42,0:20:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,204, 204, 204...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.79,0:20:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.02,0:20:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.66,0:21:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Things have gotten pretty serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.93,0:21:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole school is\Ntalking about Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.64,0:21:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would have thought that\Nhe had committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,His suicide note was printed\Nin the school paper, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.34,0:21:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can no longer\Ncontinue to deceive."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.71,0:21:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.02,0:21:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He was weighed down by\Na guilty conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for pretending to be Schuwald's son\Nto get close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.12,0:21:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He shouldn't have done it\Nin the first place
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.06,0:21:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if it was going to drive him\Nto his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.50,0:22:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you must have had\Na rough time yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.24,0:22:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.27,0:22:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We were questioned all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.61,0:22:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The reading job was called off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.08,0:22:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schuwald was very depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...Karl, let me introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.18,0:22:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in charge of Fridays.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.29,0:22:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.72,0:22:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A pleasure! I'm Karl Neumann\Nin the economics department.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.43,0:22:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Johan Liebert\Nin the School of Law.
